    <p>Get help with your Google Calendar Reminder App</p>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <h3>How do I get started?</h3>
    <p>Simply click "Sign in with Google" on the home page and grant read-only access to your Google Calendar. Once connected, you can immediately start setting up reminders for your upcoming events.</p>

    <h3>How do I enable SMS notifications?</h3>
    <p>To receive SMS reminders:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Sign in to your account</li>
      <li>Click on "Notification Settings"</li>
      <li>Enter your mobile phone number</li>
      <li>Choose "SMS" or "Both" when creating reminders for events</li>
    </ol>
    <p>By providing your phone number, you consent to receive automated text message reminders. Message and data rates may apply.</p>

    <h3>How many reminders can I set per event?</h3>
    <p>You can set multiple reminders for each calendar event. Each reminder can be configured with different timing (e.g., 5 minutes before, 1 hour before, 1 day before) and delivery method (email, SMS, or both).</p>

    <h3>Can I customize when I receive reminders?</h3>
    <p>Yes! When adding a reminder to an event, you can choose from various timing options:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>5, 10, 15, or 30 minutes before</li>
      <li>1, 2, 3, 6, or 12 hours before</li>
      <li>1 day before</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How do I stop receiving SMS messages?</h3>
    <p>You can opt out of SMS notifications by:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Texting STOP to any reminder message you receive</li>
      <li>Going to Notification Settings and changing your notification method to "Email only"</li>
      <li>Removing your phone number from your account settings</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Will I be charged for SMS messages?</h3>
    <p>We do not charge for sending SMS reminders, but standard message and data rates from your mobile carrier may apply. Check with your carrier for details about your messaging plan.</p>

    <h3>Is my calendar data safe?</h3>
    <p>Absolutely. We take your privacy seriously:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>We only request read-only access to your Google Calendar (we cannot create, modify, or delete your events)</li>
      <li>Your calendar data is used exclusively to send you reminders</li>
      <li><strong>We do not share your personal information, including your mobile phone number, with third parties or affiliates for marketing or promotional purposes</strong></li>
      <li>All data is encrypted in transit and at rest</li>
      <li>You can revoke access at any time</li>
    </ul>
    <p>See our <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_path %> for complete details.</p>

    <h3>What if a reminder doesn't arrive?</h3>
    <p>If you're not receiving reminders:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Check that your notification settings are configured correctly</li>
      <li>Verify your email address and/or phone number are correct</li>
      <li>Check your spam/junk folder for email reminders</li>
      <li>Ensure you haven't accidentally blocked our SMS number</li>
      <li>Verify the reminder hasn't already been sent (check the event card for reminder status)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Can I use this with multiple Google accounts?</h3>
    <p>Currently, you can connect one Google account at a time. If you need to switch accounts, sign out and sign in with a different Google account.</p>

    <h3>How do I delete my account?</h3>
    <p>To delete your account and all associated data:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Visit your <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Account Permissions</a></li>
      <li>Remove this application from your connected apps</li>
      <li>Click "Sign Out" in our app</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We will delete all your data, including your phone number and calendar information, within 30 days.</p>

    <h2>SMS Help Commands</h2>
    <p>You can text the following commands to any reminder message:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>STOP</strong> - Opt out of SMS notifications</li>
      <li><strong>START</strong> - Opt back in to SMS notifications</li>
      <li><strong>HELP</strong> - Get help information via SMS</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Privacy and Terms</h2>
    <p>For information about how we collect, use, and protect your data:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_path %></li>
      <li><%= link_to "Terms of Service", terms_path %></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Technical Issues</h2>
    <p>If you're experiencing technical issues:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Try signing out and signing back in</li>
      <li>Clear your browser cache and cookies</li>
      <li>Make sure you're using a supported browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)</li>
      <li>Check that your Google Calendar has upcoming events</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact Information</h2>
    <p>For issues not covered in this FAQ or to report a problem, you can reach us at:</p>
    <p style="font-size: 16px; margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Email:</strong> support@example.com</p>

    <h2>Service Provider Information</h2>
    <p>SMS messages are delivered via Twilio. For carrier-specific issues with SMS delivery, please contact your mobile carrier.</p>
  </div>

